title._content: Joe Oliver and Grant County Extension Agent, W. K. Farrell looking at cottonseed cake feeder for cattle, 1951

description._content: Original Collection: Extension and Experiment Station Communications Photograph Collection (P120) Item Number: P120:6496 Image Description: The 16 foot by 5 foot cottonseed cake self feeder was used by Joe Oliver, John Day, Oregon. The feeder holds more than 1 ton and is filled through a hinged board in the roof. Note deep overhang to prevent snow and rain from wetting the cake.
